  "texts": [
    "The robustness of agents deployed in environments with a climate different from that in which they were trained is another relevant issue (see Sects. 5.4 and 6.2).",
    "Although there were yield losses, we believe that it will depend on the case to consider whether or not these losses are negligible.",
    "On the other hand, we observed in Sects.",
    "5.5 and 6.3 that a sequential learning approach did not show improvements, but biases towards the last environment used to train the agent.",
    "While it may be due to overfitting, the usefulness of this type of training needs to be further studied."
  ],
